# Cloudflare Web Analytics token.
# Get yours at: https://dash.cloudflare.com/?to=/:account/web-analytics
# - Click "Add a site"
# - Enter: antonioppereira.github.io
# - Copy the token from the snippet shown (it's the value of "data-cf-beacon": {"token": "..."}).
#
# This is technically a public token (it appears in the rendered HTML), but
# keeping it in env lets you rotate it without a code change.
#
# Local: copy this file to .env and paste your token. The Analytics component
# only fires in production builds, so dev (`npm run dev`) won't pollute your stats.
#
# Production: set the same name as a GitHub Actions secret in the repo settings
# (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret).
PUBLIC_CF_BEACON_TOKEN=
